        {
          "id": "s0001",
          "zh": "太史公曰：五帝、三代之記，尚矣。",
          "translations": []
        },
        {
          "id": "s0002",
          "zh": "自殷以前諸侯不可得而譜，周以來乃頗可著。",
          "translations": []
        },
        {
          "id": "s0003",
          "zh": "孔子因史文次春秋，紀元年，正時日月，蓋其詳哉。",
          "translations": []
        },
        {
          "id": "s0004",
          "zh": "至於序尚書則略，無年月；",
          "translations": []
        },
        {
          "id": "s0005",
          "zh": "或頗有，然多闕，不可錄。",
          "translations": []
        },
        {
          "id": "s0006",
          "zh": "故疑則傳疑，蓋其慎也。",
          "translations": []
        }
      ],
      "translations": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "literal": "The Grand Historian says: The records of the Five Emperors and Three Dynasties are already ancient. Before the Yin dynasty, the feudal lords cannot be properly arranged in genealogical tables; since the Zhou, they can be quite well recorded. Confucius followed the historical texts to arrange the Spring and Autumn Annals, recording the first year, correcting the days and months—how detailed it is! As for arranging the Documents, it is brief, without years and months; some have them to some extent, but many are missing and cannot be recorded. Therefore, where there is doubt, transmit the doubt—this is his carefulness.",
          "idiomatic": null,
          "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
          "model": "grok-1.5"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "sentences": [
        {
          "id": "s0007",
          "zh": "余讀諜記，黃帝以來皆有年數。",
          "translations": []
        },
        {
          "id": "s0008",
          "zh": "稽其歷譜諜終始五德之傳，古文咸不同，乖異。",
          "translations": []
        },
        {
          "id": "s0009",
          "zh": "夫子之弗論次其年月，豈虛哉！",
          "translations": []
        },
        {
          "id": "s0010",
          "zh": "於是以五帝系諜、尚書集世紀黃帝以連山訖共和為世表。",
          "translations": []
        }
      ],
      "translations": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "literal": "I have read the secret records; since the Yellow Emperor, all have year numbers. Examining their calendar genealogies and secret records, the transmission of the beginning and end of the Five Virtues—all the ancient texts differ and are contradictory. That the Master did not discuss and arrange their years and months—was this in vain? Therefore, using the Five Emperors genealogical records and Documents collected generations, I made genealogical tables from the Yellow Emperor down to the Gonghe period.",
          "idiomatic": null,
          "translator": "Garrett M. Petersen (2025)",
          "model": "grok-1.5"
        }
      ]
    },
